headline: 3 Reasons to Sell RL and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: The past six months have been a windfall for Ralph Lauren’s shareholders. The company’s stock price has jumped 40%, hitting $312.58 per share. This was partly due to its solid quarterly results, and the run-up might have investors contemplating their next move.
